---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — MCP Directory"
  description="MCP Directory is an independent, weekly-updated index of 2,100+ public Model Context Protocol servers on GitHub."
>
  <section class="px-4 mx-auto max-w-2xl pt-10 pb-20 prose-invert-tight">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white">About MCP Directory</h1>

    <p class="mt-4">
      MCP Directory indexes public <a href="https://modelcontextprotocol.io" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Model Context Protocol</a>
      servers from GitHub and organizes them so AI engineers can find the right tool quickly.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-8">How it works</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      A weekly script scans GitHub for repos tagged with <code>mcp</code>, <code>model-context-protocol</code>,
      or that mention MCP in their README. We extract metadata, infer a category, and rebuild the static site.
      No tracking beyond simple privacy-friendly analytics.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-8">Free &amp; open</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      The site is free, ad-free, and has no paid placement. Listings are auto-indexed from public GitHub
      repositories and ranked only by the data — stars, recency, and category.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-8">Independence</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      MCP Directory is not affiliated with Anthropic or the MCP authors. The MCP spec and trademarks belong to their owners.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-8">Contact</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      Submit servers via <a href="/submit/">the submit form</a>. For takedown requests, listing fixes, or partnership inquiries,
      reach out via the same form (use the notes field).
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
